article.description: Pat Andree led four players in double figures with 23 points and Lehigh shot 52 percent from the field and controlled Army in an 84-53 win Saturday night.
article.headline: Lehigh buries 13 3-pointers in an 84-53 rout over Army
article.linkText: Lehigh buries 13 3-pointers in an 84-53 rout over Army
article.story: BETHLEHEM, Pa. -- Pat Andree led four players in double figures with 23 points and Lehigh shot 52 percent from the field and controlled Army in an 84-53 win Saturday night. Jordan Cohen scored 16 with eight rebounds, Lance Tejada scored 12 and Marques Wilson 10 as the Mountain Hawks had nine players enter the scoring column. Lehigh outrebounded Army 52-41 and the Black Knights struggled from the field, making 22 of 75 (29 percent). Lehigh (14-13, 9-7 Patriot League) went on a 10-0 run for 21-16 lead with 10:29 before halftime and never trailed again. Alex King's jump shot brought Army within 27-21 before Andree made a pair of 3s and Wilson added another during a 13-0 run, and Lehigh went to halftime up 40-25 and went on to finish with 13 3-pointers. Jordan Fox led Army (13-14, 6-10) with 12 points and Tommy Funk and Matt Wilson each scored 10. Army missed 7 of 10 free throws and was 6 of 34 from 3-point range.
